item.title: DHL Cargo Plane Crashes in Lithuania, Killing One
item.description: A DHL cargo plane flying from Germany to Lithuania crashed near Vilnius airport, according to an airport spokesperson.

item.title: Ukraine Clings to Shrinking Sliver of Russia, Expecting Trump to Push for Peace Talks
item.description: Moscow’s forces have launched a massive counteroffensive to retake land in the Kursk region, a potential bargaining chip for Kyiv.

item.description: Zvi Kogan was targeted in an “act of antisemitic terrorism,” Israeli authorities said.

item.title: Canadian Postal Workers Strike Drags On as Talks Fail to Break Deadlock

item.title: Chuck Woolery, Host of 'Love Connection,' Dies at 83
item.description: The genial TV host turned right-wing podcaster was an outspoken critic of the government’s pandemic response.

item.title: U.N. Reaches $300 Billion Climate Financing Deal as Trump Looms

item.description: The disappearance of a Chabad rabbi prompts fears of Israeli citizens being targeted outside of Israel.

item.description: Yet Kyiv’s missile program lacks capacity and funding, which could limit its effectiveness.
